    <section id="libpaxos_cpp.tutorial.basic_lock_service_client">
      <title><link linkend="libpaxos_cpp.tutorial.basic_lock_service_client">Lock
      service.1 - Basic client</link></title>
      <para>
        This section describes the client that connects to our distributed lock service's
        server. It describes a trivial client that executes a few lock commands and
        verifies the correct result.
      </para>
      <para>
        First, let's include our headers and define the client object.
      </para>
<programlisting xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><phrase role="preprocessor">#include</phrase> <phrase role="special">&lt;</phrase><phrase role="identifier">paxos</phrase><phrase role="special">++/</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">hpp</phrase><phrase role="special">&gt;</phrase>

<phrase role="keyword">int</phrase> <phrase role="identifier">main</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase>
<phrase role="special">{</phrase>
   <phrase role="identifier">paxos</phrase><phrase role="special">::</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase> <phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">;</phrase>
   <phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">add</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"127.0.0.1"</phrase><phrase role="special">,</phrase> <phrase role="number">1337</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
</programlisting>
      <para>
        Now that we have this client, let's attempt to lock the lock with id "foo"
        and verify that it results in the proper command:
      </para>
<programlisting xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><phrase role="identifier">assert</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">send</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"lock foo"</phrase><phrase role="special">).</phrase><phrase role="identifier">get</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase> <phrase role="special">==</phrase> <phrase role="string">"success"</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
</programlisting>
      <para>
        Now, let's try to re-acquire this lock and expect a failure:
      </para>
<programlisting xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><phrase role="identifier">assert</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">send</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"lock foo"</phrase><phrase role="special">).</phrase><phrase role="identifier">get</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase> <phrase role="special">==</phrase> <phrase role="string">"fail"</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
</programlisting>
      <para>
        However, acquiring a lock with another id should succeed:
      </para>
<programlisting xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><phrase role="identifier">assert</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">send</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"lock bar"</phrase><phrase role="special">).</phrase><phrase role="identifier">get</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase> <phrase role="special">==</phrase> <phrase role="string">"success"</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
</programlisting>
      <para>
        And re-acquiring that lock should fail:
      </para>
<programlisting xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><phrase role="identifier">assert</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">send</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"lock bar"</phrase><phrase role="special">).</phrase><phrase role="identifier">get</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase> <phrase role="special">==</phrase> <phrase role="string">"fail"</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
</programlisting>
      <para>
        Now, let's release both locks and verify it succeeds:
      </para>
<programlisting xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><phrase role="identifier">assert</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">send</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"unlock foo"</phrase><phrase role="special">).</phrase><phrase role="identifier">get</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase> <phrase role="special">==</phrase> <phrase role="string">"success"</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
<phrase role="identifier">assert</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">send</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"unlock bar"</phrase><phrase role="special">).</phrase><phrase role="identifier">get</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase> <phrase role="special">==</phrase> <phrase role="string">"success"</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
</programlisting>
      <para>
        And verify re-releasing those locks fails:
      </para>
<programlisting xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"><phrase role="identifier">assert</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">send</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"unlock foo"</phrase><phrase role="special">).</phrase><phrase role="identifier">get</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase> <phrase role="special">==</phrase> <phrase role="string">"fail"</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
<phrase role="identifier">assert</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="identifier">client</phrase><phrase role="special">.</phrase><phrase role="identifier">send</phrase> <phrase role="special">(</phrase><phrase role="string">"unlock bar"</phrase><phrase role="special">).</phrase><phrase role="identifier">get</phrase> <phrase role="special">()</phrase> <phrase role="special">==</phrase> <phrase role="string">"fail"</phrase><phrase role="special">);</phrase>
</programlisting>
      <para>
        See the <link linkend="libpaxos_cpp.tutorial.basic_lock_service_client.a00001">full
        source listing</link>
      </para>
